Vietnam’s Stocks: Bibica, Cadovimex Seafood, Phu Nhuan Jewelry

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-05-30T05:53:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-30/vietnam-s-stocks-bibica-cadovimex-seafood-phu-nhuan-jewelry.html
Shares of the following companies had
unusual moves in Vietnam trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the 11 a.m. local-time close.  The VN Index, the benchmark measure of the Ho Chi Minh City
Stock Exchange, gained for a third day, adding 0.3 percent to
412.10.  Bibica Corp. (BBC)  , a manufacturer of confectionery
products, slumped by the daily limit of 5 percent to 11,500
dong. The company will halt a cake production line for three to
four months due to a fire, it said in an exchange filing.  Cadovimex Seafood Import-Export & Processing Joint-Stock
Co. (CAD VN), a processor and trader of seafood based in the
southernmost province of Ca Mau, fell 2.6 percent to 3,800 dong.
Its 2010 loss widened to 30.2 billion dong ($1.5 million) after
an audit, compared with the 13.4 billion dong reported earlier,
Cadovimex said in a statement on the exchange’s website.  Phu Nhuan Jewelry Joint-Stock Co. (PNJ VN), the only
jewelry manufacturer on the exchange, increased 1.3 percent to
22,800 dong. Gold in  Shanghai  rose as much as 0.6 percent to an
all-time high of 319.90 yuan ($49.34) a gram today.  --Diep Ngoc Pham in Hanoi. Editor: Shiyin Chen  To contact the Bloomberg News staff on this story:
